  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "As of 2015, the **F-22 Raptor** was widely regarded as the best all-around fighter jet in the world. Developed by Lockheed Martin for the United States Air Force (USAF), the F-22 is a fifth-generation stealth fighter that excels in air superiority, ground attack, and intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) missions. Here are some key reasons for its dominance:\n\n1. **Stealth Capabilities**: The F-22's advanced stealth technology makes it nearly invisible to radar, allowing it to penetrate enemy defenses with minimal detection.\n2. **Superior Maneuverability**: With thrust-vectoring engines, the F-22 can perform extreme maneuvers, giving it an edge in dogfights.\n3. **Advanced Avionics**: The jet is equipped with cutting-edge radar, sensors, and communication systems, providing unparalleled situational awareness.\n4. **Supersonic Performance**: The F-22 can cruise at supersonic speeds without using afterburners (supercruise), making it faster and more fuel-efficient than most other jets.\n5. **Multirole Capability**: While primarily designed for air superiority, the F-22 can also perform strike missions with precision-guided munitions.\n\nOther notable contenders in 2015 included the **F-35 Lightning II**, also a fifth-generation jet, which was designed with a greater focus on multirole capabilities and affordability. However, the F-35 was still in its early stages of deployment and faced some teething issues at the time, making the F-22 the more mature and proven platform.\n\nOutside the U.S., the Russian **Sukhoi Su-35** and the European **Eurofighter Typhoon** were considered highly capable fourth-generation jets but lacked the stealth and some of the advanced technologies of the F-22. The **Chengdu J-20**, China's first fifth-generation stealth fighter, was in development but not yet fully operational by 2015.\n\nIn summary, the **F-22 Raptor** was the best all-around fighter jet in 2015, combining stealth, speed, maneuverability, and advanced technology in a way that no other aircraft could match at the time.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
